pageContext.claim: “Despite a Federal Reserve that doesn't know what it is doing - raised rates far too fast … Think of what it could have been if the Fed had gotten it right. Thousands of points higher on the Dow, and GDP in the 4’s or even 5’s.”
pageContext.analysis: There is no basis for Trump's claim that GDP growth and stock market gains would soar without higher interest rates. The Federal Reserve has raised rates to prevent the economy from overheating and falling into recession.
